02/06/84  move_quota, mq

Syntax:  mq path1 quota_change1 {... pathN quota_changeN}


Function: moves storage quota between two directories, one immediately
inferior to the other.


Arguments:
pathN
   pathname of a directory; -wd or -wdir can be used. The star
   convention CANNOT be used.
quota_changeN
   number of records to be moved between the containing directory
   quota and the pathN quota. The argument can be either positive or
   negative.  If positive, quota is moved from the containing
   directory to pathN; if negative, the move is from pathN to the
   containing directory.


Access required: The user must have modify permission on both the
directory specified by pathN and its containing directory.

